PAL Holdings, Posco, Vista Land, Pal Holdings: Asia Ex-Japan Stock Preview

-- B y   A n u c h i t   N g u y e n
-- 
2011-07-24T22:04:23Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-24/posco-vista-land-pal-holdings-asia-ex-japan-equity-preview.html
The following companies may have
unusual price changes today in Asian trading, excluding  Japan .
Stock symbols are in parentheses and share prices are from the
previous close, unless noted otherwise.  PAL Holdings Inc. (PAL)  : Philippine Airlines Inc., the
nation’s largest carrier and unit of the company, posted a so-
called “total comprehensive income” of $72.5 million in the
year ended March 31 from a loss of $14.4 million a year earlier
as passenger traffic and cargo increased, the airline said in an
emailed statement. Philippine Airlines “remains watchful of the
year ahead as fuel prices continue their uptrend” and as demand
for travel slows, it said. The stock fell 1.9 percent to 5.30
pesos.  Posco (005490 KS): The world’s third-biggest steelmaker
reported a 23 percent increase in second-quarter profit as a
recovery in demand allowed it to increase prices. Group net
income rose to 1.37 trillion won ($1.3 billion) in the three
months ended June 30 from 1.12 trillion won a year earlier, the
Pohang, South Korea-based company said in a statement. Sales
gained 58 percent to 17.05 trillion won.  Posco (005490)  rose 0.9 percent
to 474,000 won.  Vista Land & Lifescapes Inc. (VLL)  : The Philippine
builder of homes named Manuel Paolo Villar as president and
chief executive, the Manila-based company said in an e-mailed
statement Villar is the oldest son of Senator Manuel Villar, the
company’s founder. The stock gained 0.3 percent to 3.36 pesos.  Zhuhai Port Co. (000507 CH): Zhuhai’s first-half net income
rose 146 percent to 208 million yuan from an adjusted 84.7
million yuan the same period last year, according to a statement
to the Shenzhen Stock Exchange. The shares fell 0.5 percent to
13 yuan.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Anuchit Nguyen in Bangkok at 
 anguyen@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Darren Boey at   dboey@bloomberg.net . 